Package org.webpki.cbor

Class CBORObject

java.lang.Object
org.webpki.cbor.CBORObject
Direct Known Subclasses:
CBORArray, CBORBigInteger, CBORBoolean, CBORBytes, CBORFloatingPoint, CBORInteger, CBORMap, CBORNull, CBORString, CBORTag
public abstract class CBORObject extends Object
Base class for all CBOR objects.

In this implementation "object" should be regarded as equivalent to the RFC 8949 "data item".

    • checkForUnread

      public void checkForUnread() throws IOException
      Checks for unread CBOR data.

      Verifies that all data from the current object including possible child objects have been read (through calling getBytes() etc.), and throws an exception if this is not the case.

      Throws:
      IOException
      See Also:

    • decode

      public static CBORObject decode(InputStream inputStream, boolean sequenceFlag, boolean nonDeterministic, boolean constrainedKeys, Integer maxLength) throws IOException
      Decodes CBOR data with options.

      See CBORSequenceBuilder.

      Parameters:
      inputStream - Stream holding CBOR data
      sequenceFlag - Stop reading after parsing a valid CBOR object (no object returns null)
      nonDeterministic - Disable deterministic encoding check
      constrainedKeys - Limit map keys to text string and integer types, including flagging mixing of these types in map
      maxLength - Holds maximum input size in bytes or null (Integer.MAX_VALUE is assumed)
      Returns:
      CBORObject
      Throws:
      IOException
